The paper proposes a novel approach using deep reinforcement learning (DRL) for downlink power allocation in multi-cell networks. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category, as DRL is a subfield of machine learning that combines deep learning and reinforcement learning. Additionally, the paper involves optimization of wireless networks, which could fall under the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. The use of deep learning also suggests that the paper could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. Furthermore, the paper involves the use of Q-learning, which is a popular reinforcement learning algorithm, and this could suggest that the paper could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. Finally, the paper involves the optimization of a multi-cell system, which could suggest that the paper could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
